      "title": "THE PROBLEM NO ONE WANTED TO ADMIT",
      "duration_seconds": 150,
      "theme_color": "#110000",
      "narration": "We built machines that could answer questions,\nbut not machines that could understand us.\n\nWe built systems that could generate text,\nbut not systems that could remember who we are.\n\nWe built intelligence without identity.\n\nAnd for a while, we pretended that was enough.\n\nBut the truth was always there, hiding in plain sight:\n\nStateless intelligence collapses under real human complexity.\n\nIt resets.\nIt forgets.\nIt contradicts itself.\nIt cannot hold a relationship.\n\nAnd when the world became more complex,\nthe cracks became impossible to ignore.\n\nWe needed something more.\nSomething stable.\nSomething governed.\nSomething that could grow with us,\nnot just respond to us.\n\nThat is where this story begins.",
